HEADWORD: Hesperornis
<hw>Hes`pe*ror"nis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ western + <?/, <?/, a bird.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A
genus of large, extinct, wingless birds from the Cretaceous deposits of
Kansas, belonging to the Odontornithes. They had teeth, and were
essentially carnivorous swimming ostriches. Several species are known.
See <xex>Illust.</xex> in Append.</def>⟦br⟧
